Management KPI & Risk Brief – Q1 2026
Medium-sized Cosmetics FMCG Business

KPI Performance Summary
• Customer service: OTIF 91 % and overall service level 92 % are below the internal 95 % target. Premium skincare fill rate in North & East is only 84 %.
• Supply responsiveness: Stock-out rate 8 % (driven by premium skincare and budget skincare in low-sales regions). Average days of cover ranges from 4 to 34, signalling allocation imbalance.
• Planning quality: Forecast accuracy 78 % – adequate for fast-moving beauty lines should be ≥85 %. Inventory turns 5.4 and excess inventory value US $120 k confirm demand-supply mis-alignment.
• Working-capital mix:
– Short cover: Premium skincare (North 5 days, East 4 days with 7-day delay).
– Long cover: Budget makeup (25-34 days in all regions, demand falling).
Key Risks (ranked by urgency & business impact)
Premium skincare service risk in growth regions (East → demand +, North → demand +): very low cover, inbound delay, 16 % fill-rate gap; threatens primary growth engine and brand equity.
Structural excess in declining budget makeup (all regions): 25-34 days cover ties up ≈45 % of total excess inventory and suppresses turns. Obsolescence risk rising.
Chronic under-availability of budget skincare in low-sales cluster: 68 % availability, frequent stock-outs drive share loss and retail fines in price-sensitive channels.
Planning & coordination weakness: disparate spreadsheets, forecast accuracy 78 %, OTIF shortfall → systemic rather than episodic issue.
Business Impact
• Revenue / market share: Immediate sales loss risk of 7-10 % in premium skincare North & East (rising demand unmet).
• Working capital: US $120 k tied up in slow movers while fast movers starve; inventory turns stuck at 5.4 (target ≥7).
• Service image: Below-target OTIF and 8 % stock-out erode retailer confidence; premium segment most sensitive.
• Supply chain agility: Delayed inbound (East) and spreadsheet-driven decision cycle slow corrective actions by 3-5 days, limiting responsiveness to volatile demand.
Recommended Next Actions
Immediate (within 7 days)
• Expedite 300 delayed premium skincare units to East via fastest available mode and pull 150 units of premium skincare from South/West safety stock to North; raises cover to >10 days and safeguards growth revenue.

Medium term (within 30 days)
• Launch a SKU-level inventory re-balancing & run-down plan:
– Freeze new purchase orders for budget makeup for one review cycle.
– Transfer 10-15 % of excess budget makeup stock from North/West to low-sales cluster to backfill gaps in promotional bundles.
– Target to free ≥US $70 k of working capital and lift inventory turns to 6.5.

Highest-priority KPI issue
• Premium skincare fill rate (currently 84 %) – because it combines highest margin, fastest growth, and largest immediate revenue risk.

Cross-team coordination requirement
• Single demand & inventory dashboard: mandate that Supply Chain, Sales, and Inventory teams migrate from separate spreadsheets to a shared cloud-based sheet (or interim Power BI view) with daily automatic data refresh; eliminates version lags that currently delay allocation decisions and OTIF recovery.
